\begin{abstract}
We study theoretically the optics in undoped direct gap semiconductors which are strongly
driven in the THz regime. We calculate the optical sideband generation due to nonlinear mixing of
the THz field and the near infrared probe. Starting with an inversion symmetric microscopic
Hamiltonian we include the THz field nonperturbatively using non-equilibrium Green function
techniques. We find that a self induced relativistic spin-THz field coupling
 locally breaks the inversion symmetry, resulting in the formation of odd sidebands which 
otherwise are absent.
\end{abstract}
